==English==
===Etymology===
From Hebrew [[דונם]] ''(dûnām)'' or Arabic {{ARchar|[[دونم]]}} (dūnum) < Turkish [[dönüm]] < [[dönmek]] ‘to go round’.

===Pronunciation===
{{IPA|/'dʊnəm/}}

===Noun===
'''dunam'''

# a measure of land in the Ottoman Empire and successive states, including Israel, where it corresponds to about 900 square [[metres]] in Palestine, or about 2500 square meters in Iraq.